Динамика Participation rate (pr) по неделям.¶

In [70]:
pr = data.groupby(['year', 'week']).agg(all_customers=('customer_id', 'nunique')).reset_index()
pr_loyal = data.query('loyalty == 1').groupby(['year', 'week']).agg(loyal_customers=('customer_id', 'nunique')).reset_index()
pr = pr.merge(pr_loyal, on='week').drop(columns=['year_x', 'year_y'])
pr['pr'] = pr['loyal_customers'] / pr['all_customers']
pr = pr.set_index('week')
pr.style.format({'pr':'{:.2f}'})

def categorize_bill(row):
    if row['avg_bill'] < small_bill:
        return 'small'
    elif small_bill <= row['avg_bill'] <= medium_bill:
        return 'medium'
    else:
        return 'large'

#   LTV  
def get_ltv(profiles, data, dimensions=[]):
    dimensions = ['loyal', 'year'] + dimensions
    
    last_suitable_acquisition_date = observation_date - timedelta(days=horizon_days - 1)
    profiles = profiles.query('dt <= @last_suitable_acquisition_date').copy()
    
    result_raw = profiles.merge(data_clean[['customer_id', 'date', 'total']], on='customer_id')
    
    result_raw['lifetime'] = (result_raw['date'] - result_raw['dt']).dt.days
    result_raw['lifetime_weeks'] = round(result_raw['lifetime'] / 7, 0)
    result_raw['lifetime_weeks'] = result_raw['lifetime_weeks'].astype('int')
    result_raw['week'] = result_raw['dt'].dt.isocalendar().week
    max_lifetime = result_raw['lifetime_weeks'].max()
    
    result_grouped = (result_raw.pivot_table(index=['loyal', 'year', 'week'],
                                         columns='lifetime_weeks',
                                         values='total',
                                         aggfunc='sum').
                  fillna(0)
                     )
    
    cohort_sizes = result_raw.groupby(dimensions).agg(cohort_size=('customer_id', 'nunique'))
    
    result_grouped = cohort_sizes.merge(result_grouped, on=dimensions)
    
    #  200 .      
    result_grouped['fees'] = 0
    part_1 = result_grouped.query('loyal == False').copy()
    part_2 = result_grouped.query('loyal == True').copy()
    part_2['fees'] = part_2['cohort_size'] * pay_per_month # ,    4-   0-
    result_grouped = part_1.append(part_2)
    for x in range(0, max_lifetime+1, 4):
        result_grouped[x] = result_grouped[x].add(result_grouped['fees'], axis=0)
    
    result_grouped = result_grouped.drop(columns=['cohort_size', 'fees']).cumsum(axis=1)
    result_grouped['cohort_size'] = cohort_sizes
    
    result_grouped = result_grouped.div(result_grouped['cohort_size'], axis=0).drop(columns=['cohort_size'])
    
    result_grouped = result_grouped[list(range(horizon_weeks))]
        
    return result_raw, result_grouped
